ArrayList<Byte> allBytes = new ArraList<Byte>();

Big Endian is where the least significant byte is towards the right
Little Endian is the opposite

When doing your RGB calculations, you have to input it as BGR rather than RGB because the BMP file is input backwards
i.e. for loops would be backwards where instead of left to right, top to bottom, it is left to right, bottom to top

Possible Usage for input 
__________________________________________________________________________
JTextField red = new JTextField(5);
        JTextField green = new JTextField(5);
        JTextField blue = new JTextField(5);

        JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "Welcome to the Pixel Icon Program Assignement!");

        JPanel pixelPanel = new JPanel();
            pixelPanel.add(new JLabel("r:"));
            pixelPanel.add(red);
            pixelPanel.add(Box.createHorizontalStrut(10));
            pixelPanel.add(new JLabel("g:"));
            pixelPanel.add(green);
            pixelPanel.add(Box.createHorizontalStrut(10));
            pixelPanel.add(new JLabel("b:"));
            pixelPanel.add(blue);
            pixelPanel.add(Box.createHorizontalStrut(10));
        
        int output = JOptionPane.showConfirmDialog(null, pixelPanel, "Please enter your desired RGB values: ", JOptionPane.OK_CANCEL_OPTION);
        if (output == JOptionPane.OK_OPTION) {
            r = Integer.parseInt(red);
            JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(Integer.parseInt(r));

        }       